verbose_text: In addition, myocardial AngII can promote the release of catecholamines of the sympathetic nerve endings, promote the synthesis of mitochondrial and expression of proto-oncogene in cardiomyocytes through the receptors on the nucleus, and stimulate the growth and proliferation of cardiomyocytes, leading to cardiac hypertrophy [XREF_BIBR].
